contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:29.166 --> 08:31.166
Nice move, Booker.

08:31.168 --> 08:32.801
Okay, back to work.

08:32.803 --> 08:35.303
You mean back to Skwerk.

08:35.304 --> 08:37.422
Hey, Yoda.

08:37.424 --> 08:39.256
Do you know where
the interns sit?

08:39.259 --> 08:42.644
Yeah. I do, because that
is where I sit.

08:42.645 --> 08:44.762
It's this way.

08:44.764 --> 08:46.147
My name's Liam.

08:46.149 --> 08:47.765
Zita.

08:47.767 --> 08:49.767
So, what brings you
to Skwerkel, Zita?

08:49.769 --> 08:51.686
Uh, last week I popped
the wrong pills

08:51.688 --> 08:53.104
and wrecked my dad's
precious Tesla.

08:53.106 --> 08:55.023
So it was either
an internship here

08:55.025 --> 08:56.691
or boarding school
in Florida.

08:56.693 --> 09:00.078
And not Miami.
Tampa.

09:00.080 --> 09:03.498
So here I am. Yay.

09:03.500 --> 09:04.782
Well, we're
in the same boat,

09:04.784 --> 09:06.501
'cause I, too,
am here against my will.

09:06.503 --> 09:08.920
Right.

09:10.457 --> 09:12.457
The school converted
the football field

09:12.459 --> 09:14.459
into an organic
vegetable garden.

09:14.461 --> 09:16.794
- You got to be kidding.
- That's just the beginning.

09:16.796 --> 09:19.097
They replaced AP calculus
with yarn arts.

09:19.099 --> 09:21.132
Everyone had to knit a sweater
for the final.

09:21.134 --> 09:24.552
I couldn't make
this shi... stuff up.

09:24.554 --> 09:25.970
Miss Cooper,

09:25.972 --> 09:28.056
you seem as horrified
by this place as I am.

09:28.058 --> 09:30.725
How were you possibly elected
president of your class?

09:30.727 --> 09:33.611
Because I've learned how
to manipulate these idiots.

09:33.613 --> 09:36.064
- And, boy, do you need my help.
- Oh, do I?

09:36.066 --> 09:37.649
You've got to get the students
on your side

09:37.651 --> 09:38.983
before there's a protest.

09:38.985 --> 09:41.374
Trust me, we're barely
in class as it is.

09:41.409 --> 09:46.708
_

09:46.743 --> 09:48.293
Hey, boo-boo.

09:48.295 --> 09:49.494
Miss me?

09:49.496 --> 09:51.996
Uh, Amy, what are you
doing here?

09:51.998 --> 09:55.466
Oh, well, it took me four years
to read <i>Fifty Shades,</i>

09:55.468 --> 09:58.336
and I figured
you'd want it back, stat.

09:58.338 --> 10:00.004
What is happening here?

10:00.006 --> 10:01.806
Where are all your things?
You love things.

10:01.808 --> 10:04.759
Uh, you know,
spring cleaning.

10:04.761 --> 10:06.594
Out with the old,
in with the new.

10:06.596 --> 10:09.013
Oh. Sorry.
I, um... I can come back.

10:09.015 --> 10:10.732
Why are you here now?
Who's this?

10:11.685 --> 10:15.019
Uh... Felix here

10:15.021 --> 10:16.854
is my new...

10:16.856 --> 10:19.240
GBF.

10:19.242 --> 10:21.659
He's helping me take
my wardrobe from drab to fab.

10:21.661 --> 10:23.161
Isn't that right, Felix?

10:23.163 --> 10:24.862
Yes, I am.

10:24.864 --> 10:26.197
And not only am I gay,

10:26.199 --> 10:28.249
I am also
a walking stereotype.

10:29.536 --> 10:31.035
Oh, you're
so dramatic, Felix.

10:31.037 --> 10:32.870
Uh, we have a lot
of work to do.

10:32.872 --> 10:35.206
So I will call you
tomorrow, yeah?

10:35.208 --> 10:36.541
But...

10:36.543 --> 10:39.043
Yeah.
All right. Bye.

10:40.880 --> 10:43.798
I can't believe you told her
I was gay.

10:43.800 --> 10:45.580
Do you think she bought it?

10:45.721 --> 10:47.201
Students of Hester High,

10:47.236 --> 10:48.577
there are certain
personal freedoms

10:48.612 --> 10:50.456
you will no longer
be able to enjoy.

10:50.491 --> 10:52.785
Are you tired of being treated
like a criminal?

10:52.820 --> 10:55.135
I'm Lauren Cooper,
and I feel the same way.

10:55.137 --> 10:57.354
I mean, what's the point
of having lockers

10:57.356 --> 10:59.389
if there are no doors on them,
am I right?

10:59.391 --> 11:01.975
We're not allowed to park
on campus anymore.

11:01.977 --> 11:04.978
And worst of all,
we have to carry these.

11:04.980 --> 11:06.480
It's inhumane.

11:06.482 --> 11:08.482
Why should all of us be punished
for the crimes of a few?

11:08.484 --> 11:10.534
That's why I worked
with Principal Turner

11:10.536 --> 11:14.538
to create Hester's
new Verified Program.

11:14.540 --> 11:18.826
Now I can drive to school
and use a normal backpack.

11:18.828 --> 11:21.044
I have all of the freedoms
I enjoyed before.

11:21.046 --> 11:22.996
And getting verified
is simple.

11:22.998 --> 11:24.498
Just sign
the new code of conduct,

11:24.500 --> 11:27.751
get fingerprinted,
and agree to random drug tests,

11:27.753 --> 11:29.553
because if we have
nothing to hide,

11:29.555 --> 11:31.054
what's the big deal?

11:31.056 --> 11:33.891
"What's the big deal"?
Is she serious?

11:33.893 --> 11:35.893
Hey, nobody's going
to fall for that.

11:35.895 --> 11:37.895
Congratulations.
You're verified.

11:37.897 --> 11:39.646
What is happening?

11:39.648 --> 11:41.932
Hey, Shane, have you met Karma's
new mysterious gay friend?

11:41.934 --> 11:44.401
Are you kidding me?
Is he full of witty retorts?

11:44.403 --> 11:46.987
How's his fashion sense?
Is he cute? Cuter than me?

11:46.989 --> 11:49.523
I don't know.
I only met him once.

11:49.525 --> 11:50.774
- His name is Felix.
- Felix.

11:50.776 --> 11:52.993
Oh, the new guy
in my yarn arts class?

11:52.995 --> 11:55.662
Oh, thank God he's not gay.

11:55.664 --> 11:57.164
You're sure?

11:57.166 --> 11:59.783
Trust me.
My gaydar is 100% accurate.

11:59.785 --> 12:01.201
Well, with guys.

12:01.203 --> 12:03.170
If that's true, then why
would he fake being gay?

12:03.172 --> 12:05.088
Yeah. Who would do
such a terrible thing?

12:05.090 --> 12:07.207
He's Karma-ing Karma.

12:07.209 --> 12:09.960
He's pretending to be gay
so he can gain her trust

12:09.962 --> 12:11.428
and seduce her.

12:11.430 --> 12:13.213
Uh-huh.
Will you excuse me one second?

12:13.215 --> 12:15.015
Hi, Brenda.

12:15.017 --> 12:16.466
Thumbprint.

12:16.468 --> 12:18.635
Brenda, what the [bleep]?
You're getting verified?

12:18.637 --> 12:21.104
I'm sorry, Shane.
I just really need the parking.

12:21.106 --> 12:22.522
You should join her.
It's easy.

12:22.524 --> 12:24.608
Just click here to accept
the terms and conditions.

12:24.610 --> 12:27.245
If you don't mind,
I'd prefer to read them first.

12:27.916 --> 12:30.530
What?

12:30.532 --> 12:32.399
Have any of guys read this?

12:32.401 --> 12:34.701
This is longer than
my grandma's Christmas letter.

12:34.703 --> 12:36.403
They want us to play
by their rules.

12:36.405 --> 12:38.989
But Hester High has always been
about breaking the rules.

12:38.991 --> 12:40.874
We question tradition.
We trust each other.

12:40.876 --> 12:43.076
We stand up for the little guy.
Can I get an amen, Brenda?

12:43.078 --> 12:46.079
- Amen.
- You guys, there's no need

12:46.081 --> 12:48.165
for another silly protest.
They never work anyway.

12:48.167 --> 12:50.717
Maybe that's because
they've never been

12:50.719 --> 12:52.052
as epic as this one.

12:52.054 --> 12:54.471
Fellow students,
if Principal Turner

12:54.473 --> 12:56.256
wants to strip us
of our rights,

12:56.258 --> 12:59.309
then maybe we should strip
to protect them.

12:59.311 --> 13:02.262
Naked protest!
Naked protest!

13:02.264 --> 13:06.872
Naked protest! Naked protest!
Naked protest!

13:07.046 --> 13:08.804
And then, as if the day
wasn't bad enough,

13:08.839 --> 13:10.978
we had to use
the service elevator.

13:14.462 --> 13:15.661
Oh, son.

13:15.663 --> 13:17.246
I dropped by to tell you

13:17.248 --> 13:19.131
I heard you're doing great work,
and you're late.

13:19.133 --> 13:20.716
What are the odds?

13:20.718 --> 13:22.468
I was held up at school.

13:22.470 --> 13:26.923
Mm. Well, luckily, Zita's
been a delightful distraction.

13:30.595 --> 13:32.562
You didn't tell me
your dad was the CEO.

13:32.564 --> 13:34.263
He's kind of hot.

13:34.265 --> 13:36.516
What? It's true.

13:36.518 --> 13:38.434
You could tell
he'd be into it.

13:38.436 --> 13:41.153
- Oh!
- Sheesh. Such a prude.

13:41.155 --> 13:42.939
Trust me, not a prude.

13:42.941 --> 13:44.440
And stay far away
from that man.

13:44.442 --> 13:46.492
He eats children's souls
for breakfast.

13:46.494 --> 13:48.110
Wow.

13:48.112 --> 13:50.580
You really don't
like him.

13:50.582 --> 13:53.616
- Booker, Skwerking hard?
- Hardly Skwerking.

13:55.203 --> 13:57.336
These people actually
enjoy working here.

13:57.338 --> 13:59.956
- I can't piss all over that.
- Hmm.

13:59.958 --> 14:01.591
Well, if you really
hate it so much,

14:01.593 --> 14:04.210
then why are you here?

14:04.212 --> 14:05.545
That is a long story.

14:05.547 --> 14:08.214
Sounds juicy.
Take your time.

14:08.216 --> 14:10.967
Embellish the good parts.

14:10.969 --> 14:12.885
Oh, come on.
You can trust me.

14:12.887 --> 14:14.887
Who am I going to tell?
All my friends are in rehab.

14:14.889 --> 14:19.358
Okay.
Um, where do I begin?

14:19.360 --> 14:22.695
All right, Hester, when I say
"We have nothing to hide,"

14:22.697 --> 14:24.530
everyone take off
your clothes.

14:24.532 --> 14:26.198
N-U-D-E!

14:26.200 --> 14:28.701
You can't take my rights
from me!

14:28.703 --> 14:30.536
N-U-D-E!

14:30.538 --> 14:32.538
You can't take my rights
from me!

14:32.540 --> 14:33.539
N-U-D-E!

14:33.541 --> 14:35.658
You can't take my rights
from me!

14:35.660 --> 14:37.543
N-U-D-E!

14:37.545 --> 14:39.078
You can't take my rights
from me!

14:39.080 --> 14:40.463
- We need to talk.
- N-U-D-E!

14:40.465 --> 14:42.048
You can't take my rights
from me!

14:42.050 --> 14:45.134
Lauren, it's not too late.
Go tell them you made a mistake.

14:45.136 --> 14:46.552
But I didn't, Wendy.

14:46.554 --> 14:48.554
I support everything
Principal Turner is doing.

14:48.556 --> 14:50.806
You're not the same
candidate I voted for.

14:53.845 --> 14:55.261
- Lauren.
- What the [bleep]

14:55.263 --> 14:56.679
- are you doing here?
- You blocked my calls.

14:56.681 --> 14:58.180
I need to tell you
that I lied to you.

14:58.182 --> 15:00.399
Yeah, I know.
How stupid do you think I am?

15:00.401 --> 15:03.152
No. When you asked
if any of it was real,

15:03.154 --> 15:06.355
I only said no because
my boss was listening.

15:06.357 --> 15:08.157
I don't know what game
you're playing,

15:08.159 --> 15:10.326
but it's not
going to work.

15:11.863 --> 15:13.195
N-U-D-E!

15:13.197 --> 15:14.947
You can't take my rights
from me!

15:14.949 --> 15:17.750
All right, students!

15:17.752 --> 15:19.251
You have ten seconds
to disperse.

15:19.253 --> 15:21.253
After that,
everyone here

15:21.255 --> 15:23.339
will receive Saturday detention
for a month.

15:23.341 --> 15:25.207
Is he for real?

15:27.211 --> 15:29.345
I know you all
hate these new rules.

15:29.347 --> 15:30.880
A real politician
would get up here

15:30.882 --> 15:32.515
and tell you they hate them too,
but I won't pander,

15:32.517 --> 15:34.884
especially when that's not
how I feel.

15:34.886 --> 15:37.436
Hester isn't the same place
it used to be.

15:37.438 --> 15:40.389
Nobody knows that
better than me.

15:42.193 --> 15:45.853
We were humiliated.
We were used.

15:47.624 --> 15:49.899
We were betrayed.

15:51.486 --> 15:53.152
These rules are here
to protect us,

15:53.154 --> 15:56.405
because we can't let
our guard down like that again.

15:56.407 --> 15:59.158
Protect us from what, Lauren?

15:59.160 --> 16:01.243
We have nothing to hide.

16:07.835 --> 16:09.418
What the [bleep]?

16:09.420 --> 16:10.920
And even though
all she wants to be

16:10.922 --> 16:12.421
is friends with benefits
right now,

16:12.423 --> 16:14.640
I know that if I wait it out,
she'll forgive me.

16:14.642 --> 16:17.093
Mm, I hate
to be blunt, but...

16:17.095 --> 16:20.062
Actually, I love to be blunt,
because I speak the truth,

16:20.064 --> 16:22.264
and you need to hear it.
Give up.

16:22.266 --> 16:23.733
No, no, no.
You don't know her.

16:23.735 --> 16:25.735
I don't need to.
You screwed her best friend.

16:25.737 --> 16:27.236
Game over.
It's a lost cause.

16:27.238 --> 16:29.739
Not us, okay?
We have something special.

16:29.741 --> 16:32.024
Oh, Liam, how can be so rich
and so naïve?

16:33.494 --> 16:35.995
5:00.
We're free.

16:40.284 --> 16:41.617
Whoa. Hey, hey.

16:41.619 --> 16:44.170
I just had
to get you alone.

16:44.172 --> 16:45.454
I...

16:45.456 --> 16:47.339
can't stop thinking
about you.

16:47.341 --> 16:49.258
I get mistaken
for other people a lot.

16:49.260 --> 16:50.793
I have a pretty common face.

16:53.181 --> 16:54.797
Come on.

16:54.799 --> 16:56.932
Tell me you didn't feel
the connection

16:56.934 --> 16:58.601
between us last night.

16:58.603 --> 17:00.686
It was electric.

17:00.688 --> 17:02.805
It was?

17:02.807 --> 17:04.773
I mean, it was...

17:04.776 --> 17:06.008
so electric.

17:06.010 --> 17:08.194
But I thought
you were a lesbian.

17:08.195 --> 17:10.061
Ah, ah, ah, ah.

17:10.064 --> 17:12.481
I've never
labeled myself.

17:12.483 --> 17:14.900
I'm more attracted
to the person.

17:14.902 --> 17:17.319
And you are a person

17:17.320 --> 17:20.823
to whom I am definitely
attracted.

17:20.825 --> 17:23.325
And I think the feeling
is mutual.

17:23.327 --> 17:26.545
If only you weren't gay.

17:27.835 --> 17:29.665
Uh, yeah.

17:29.667 --> 17:31.967
Um, about that.

17:31.969 --> 17:34.170
What the [bleep]
is going on?

17:36.396 --> 17:39.916
Is it your goal to seduce
every guy in my life?

17:39.951 --> 17:41.482
Just when I thought
I could trust you again.

17:41.517 --> 17:45.253
You can. I was just exposing
Felix for the fraud that he is.

17:45.255 --> 17:47.589
He's straight.
He was only pretending to be gay

17:47.591 --> 17:50.759
- so he could seduce you.
- Whoa! What? Wait a second.

17:50.761 --> 17:52.477
I am straight, yeah.

17:52.479 --> 17:54.980
But I would never
do something like that.

17:54.982 --> 17:57.065
What kind of person would?

17:59.436 --> 18:01.486
Well, I can't believe

18:01.488 --> 18:02.821
you lied to me.

18:05.109 --> 18:07.242
Okay.
No, I'm sorry.

18:07.244 --> 18:08.694
I'm sorry, I can't go along
with this anymore.

18:08.696 --> 18:10.529
If you're not going
to tell her, then I will.

18:11.938 --> 18:13.782
Tell me what?

18:13.784 --> 18:16.668
Why I was in her bedroom
last night.

18:16.670 --> 18:18.954
Because...

18:18.956 --> 18:20.789
it's not my bedroom
anymore.

18:20.791 --> 18:22.624
It's his.

18:24.094 --> 18:25.460
There we go.

18:25.462 --> 18:28.130
I'm going to leave
you two alone.

18:30.968 --> 18:33.507
I don't understand.

18:35.305 --> 18:37.856
Since the drug bust,
we're broke...

18:37.858 --> 18:42.277
so broke that we had to rent out
our house to Felix's family.

18:42.279 --> 18:44.279
So we're basically homeless,
only we own a home.

18:44.281 --> 18:47.282
We just can't afford
to live in it.

18:48.485 --> 18:50.786
I'm sorry.
Why didn't you tell me?

18:50.788 --> 18:53.989
I'm living in the juice truck in
my backyard. It's humiliating.

18:53.991 --> 18:57.159
There's nothing humiliating
about it. It's not your fault.

18:57.161 --> 18:59.795
Now, those bangs you got
in fourth grade,

18:59.797 --> 19:01.496
that was humiliating.

19:02.833 --> 19:05.050
You can get through this,
but you have to let me help.

19:05.052 --> 19:08.503
But we just got through
some really heavy stuff.

19:08.505 --> 19:10.172
Exactly.

19:10.174 --> 19:12.674
And we're so much
stronger because of it.

19:12.676 --> 19:14.226
You're my best friend.

19:14.228 --> 19:16.428
We don't need these childish
necklaces to prove it.

19:16.430 --> 19:18.063
I don't think
they're childish.

19:18.065 --> 19:21.016
I lost mine when we were moving
everything into storage.

19:24.334 --> 19:26.104
Well...

19:26.106 --> 19:28.190
we can share mine.

19:28.192 --> 19:29.241
Really?

19:29.243 --> 19:31.610
Mm-hmm.

19:31.612 --> 19:35.113
Ooh, it'll be like
<i>The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants.</i>

19:35.115 --> 19:36.698
No, it's not.

19:38.142 --> 19:39.675
Hey, Karma?

19:41.205 --> 19:43.338
Hey, hey, I know it's late,

19:43.340 --> 19:46.374
but I just wanted
to tell you

19:46.376 --> 19:49.344
that I told a friend
our story today,

19:49.346 --> 19:53.932
and they called me naïve because
I still have hope for us.

19:53.934 --> 19:56.718
I love you,
and I'm not giving up.

19:56.720 --> 20:00.105
And if you can't find
your hope right now,

20:00.107 --> 20:01.723
then that's okay,

20:01.725 --> 20:05.393
because I have enough
for us both.

20:05.395 --> 20:09.147
Look, buddy, I don't know
what you heard,

20:09.149 --> 20:10.365
but I'm not gay.

20:10.367 --> 20:12.567
What are you doing
in Karma's room?

20:12.569 --> 20:14.569
You should talk to her
about that tomorrow.

20:18.075 --> 20:20.742
Felix.

20:20.744 --> 20:22.043
Who was that?

20:22.045 --> 20:23.712
Wrong number, Dad.

20:23.714 --> 20:26.248
Don't worry about it.

